{
  "texts": [
    "This creates new opportunities for identity theft, blackmail, and other fraud.",
    "Furthermore, the sensitivity of biometric data means that its breach would be uniquely damaging to users' physical and mental safety, as they would know that they are more vulnerable to identity theft and other ramifications, and that a platform entrusted with their data-or, worse, one that collected it surreptitiously-had allowed it to leak (Solove, 2006).",
    "14 Issues related to biometric data straddle the line between informational and decisional privacy, but we chose to categorize them under informational privacy because they relate more to general surveillance concerns.",
    "Issues associated with the monitoring of avatar actions, however, will be discussed under decisional privacy because the primary impact of that surveillance is deterring certain actions.",
    "Decisional privacy concerns the freedom from unwanted interference in decisions and actions (Roessler, 2005, 9)."
  ]
}